node.text: Ranch is far and away the most popular salad dressing in the United States. But it's also so much more than that. It's a dipping sauce. A Halloween costume. And (probably) the most memed condiment on the Internet. But how did an Alaskan plumber stumble upon the idea? Why did the sauce get the name "ranch," in the first place?
